Whisk together oyster sauce, ginger, soy sauce, chile paste, and 2 tablespoons of the water in small bowl. Heat oil in wok or large nonstick skillet over high heat. Add Broccolini and stir-fry 3 minutes. Add remaining 3 tablespoons water and stir-fry 2 minutes. Add steak, scallions, and oyster sauce mixture and stir-fry 1 minute or until beef is rosy and just cooked through. Stir in walnuts and serve immediately.